The paper focuses on detecting action-objects from a first-person camera using a predictive model that integrates visual appearance and 3D spatial layout cues. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and recognition, as well as robotics (RO) and artificial intelligence (AI) for understanding human-object interactions. The model is also designed to learn a spatial distribution of the action-objects in the first-person data, which could be relevant to machine learning (LG) and human-computer interaction (HC) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.HC.
